## The Core Concept
Modern computing is hitting a physical wall. Shrinking electronic transistors down to the nanometer scale has become unsustainably expensive, traps extreme heat, and creates massive data bottlenecks across traditional copper motherboard traces. 

**Project OVAL-GLASS** flips the script. Instead of scaling down using expensive silicon cleanrooms, this architecture scales **up** using widely available, high-purity, upcycled television display glass (aluminosilicate glass) as a macro-scale substrate. By routing data inside the glass using continuous-wave, multi-color lasers arranged in the proprietary **KARTUNE Nested Oval-Glass Matrix**, we eliminate the need for a traditional electronic clock, eliminate internal interconnect heat, and dramatically level the playing field for high-speed AI matrix math and quantum co-processing.
